MIT/GNU Scheme is an implementation of the Scheme programming language,
providing an interpreter, compiler, source-code debugger, integrated Emacs-like
editor, and a large runtime library. MIT/GNU Scheme is best suited to
programming large applications with a rapid development cycle.

  ENABLE_DEBUGGING=yes|no (default: no)     Compile with debugging support 
  ENABLE_X11=yes|no       (default: yes)    Add support for x11 
  ENABLE_EDWIN=yes|no     (default: yes)    Add support for the Edwin editor 
  ENABLE_IMAIL=yes|no     (default: yes)    Add support for the Imail mail reader (implies ENABLE_EDWIN=yes)
  ENABLE_HTML=yes|no      (default: no)     Builds html documentation
  ENABLE_PDF=yes|no       (default: no)     Builds pdf documentation (requires texlive)
